  210\t\n   211\tGitButler mode is more nuanced:\n   212\t\n   213\t- there may be multiple applied branches/stacks at the same time\n   214\t- there may be zero applied branches\n   215\t- stacked branches may mean both `bottom-refactor` and `top-feature` are\n   216\t  present, while the agent session is only relevant to `top-feature`\n   217\t- two applied branches such as `my-feature` and `other-stuff` may coexist even\n   218\t  when only one is relevant to the session\n   219\t\n   220\tDo not store a separate `checked_out_refs` field. It duplicates the stack/branch\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:20:09.976Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}